## `mobile-h5/` — Vite + React

**Stack:** Vite 6, React 18, react-router-dom 6, **antd-mobile**, ECharts (on-demand registration), Axios, dayjs, i18n under **`src/i18n/`**.

**Typical layout:** `src/api/`, `src/auth/`, `src/components/`, `src/dashboard/`, `src/i18n/`, `src/pages/`, `src/utils/`.

**API:** browser uses **`/v1/...`**; dev proxy **`VITE_DEV_API_TARGET`** (see `.env.example`). Login **`POST /v1/users/login`**; **`Authorization: <token>`** on other calls (align with PC).

**UI:** mobile-first; match existing theme; register only needed ECharts parts.

Apply all **universal** rules above (waterfalls, barrels, lazy heavy charts, strict `===`, English comments, i18n for visible copy).

---

## `server/` — Fastify mock API

**Stack:** Fastify 5, `@fastify/swagger`, TypeScript, JSON under **`data/store/`**.

**Layout:** `src/routes/` (one route file per path), `src/store/` (one module per JSON basename), `src/lib/` helpers.

Handlers stay thin; OpenAPI in sync with routes; commit **`*.example.json`**, not gitignored runtime JSON.

Use **`async`/`await`**, validate inputs, return envelopes compatible with **`mobile-h5`** / PC.

Apply universal habits: parallel independent IO where relevant, strict equality, English comments and OpenAPI text.

---

## `pc/` — additional rules only in that repo

For **Umi**, **MUI**, **TanStack Query** usage in PC, **`config/routes`**, **`src/locales`** (en/zh/ru), **`fluent-*` aliases**, **MUI import exceptions**, **`.eslintrc*` / `check:import`**, **`scripts/auto-test/.testrules`**, **container vs page folder layout**, and other PC-only details, read and follow **`pc/.cursorrules`** in full.
